    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-02-13T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-02-13T16:00:00-05:00" n="500"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d500">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.00/3802: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Consul at Vladivostok</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_CJK1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caldwell</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-02-13T16:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 13, 1919, 4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your February 4, 1 p.m. Department believes inadvisable that this Government
                    should be represented in negotiations between <persName corresp="#p_KAAV1"
                        >Kolchak</persName> and <persName>Semenoff</persName>. Advise Consul
                    General, Omsk.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_PW1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
